The paper discusses the reproducibility of machine learning algorithms designed for human health, which involves a combination of computer science and medical research. The focus on reproducibility suggests a strong emphasis on machine learning (cs.LG) and potentially computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. The use of health data also suggests a potential fit with the sub-categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and computational engineering (cs.CE). Finally, the paper proposes recommendations for the ML4H research community, which suggests a potential fit with the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
